Edited April 17, 2022 by AN_HAMSTER_IS_ON_SATURN_V

I've looked at your logs and the first problem I can see is Sigma Dimensions throwing an exception, which then causes Kopernicus to fail to load properly and that generates literally millions of lines of exceptions in the logs to the extent that your log file is over 200MB in size. If you had posted a mod list then I might be able to point you at specific mods that could be causing this issue; you can get a mod list easily through CKAN by clicking File > save installed mod list and saving the text file which will contain every mod and their versions. My initial suspicion is that you're using an old, outdated mod somewhere which is causing the failures to occur. Check any planet packs you're using to ensure that they're compatible with 

There are also a huge number of exceptions caused by KSP-AVC, which you should probably remove entirely.

You also seem to have two ModuleManagers? 4.2.1 and 2.5.0 from what I see in the logs. You should only ever have one ModuleManager and it should be inside KSP/GameData and the newest version (with the highest number), so delete any and all duplicates you find.

 

OK, I just looked at the video and you're clearly using many very outdated mods- some were made for KSP 1.4, 1.3 and even 1.2. This is a bad idea as these old mods are very unlikely to work but very likely to break things: KSP has had Unity version upgrades that make mods compiled against the older versions unable to run.

I suggest you completely destroy this copy of KSP and start from scratch. If you want to play with RO and RP-1, there's a special express install available on CKAN that can install all the necessary mods in a few clicks; however I don't think your PC will be able to run the game with those mods, or if it does it'll be painfully slow.
